After clashing with Jim Lee on X-Men v1 (1991), Chris Claremont left the series after only 3 issues and decided to focus on other projects, thus ending his incredible nearly 17-year run with writing the X-Men. He quickly returned to them, however, and while Grant Morrison was busy writing his own unique interpretation in New X-Men, Claremont was simultaneously given this title to work on and make his own. Featuring a line-up of old and new X-Men including a few icons such as Storm, Beast, Rogue and Gambit and the soon-to-be renegade X-Man Bishop, this title was a continuation of sorts of Claremont's previous work and contained many interesting storylines. This torrent collects all issues 01-46 as well as the Savage Land mini (01-04). NOTE: SAVAGE LAND IS MEANT TO BE READ AFTER ISSUE 4 OF THE MAIN TITLE. Otherwise, you may be confused as to what is going on. Massive thanks to AnHeroGold-Empire for these digital copies, please seed and enjoy! :-)
